President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key administration posts. Robert Perciasepe was nominated for Deputy Administrator of the Environmental Protection Agency, Thelma Melendez de Santa Ana for Assistant Secretary for Elementary and Secondary Education at the Department of Education, Colin Scott Fulton for General Counsel at the Environmental Protection Agency, J. Michael Gilmore for Director of Operational Test & Evaluation at the Department of Defense, Bart Chilton for Commissioner of the Commodity Futures Trading Commission, and Cranston Mitchell for Commissioner of the U.S. Parole Commission at the Department of Justice. Additionally, President Obama announced that Isaac Fulwood will be designated as Chairman of the U.S. Parole Commission. The President expressed gratitude for their decision to join his administration and highlighted their expertise in various fields.